                            "html": "<b>CR </b>3; <b>Size </b>Tiny; <b>Hit Dice </b>4d12<br/><b>Speed </b>40 ft., burrow 30 ft.<br/><b>Natural Armor </b>+4; <b>Breath Weapon </b>line, 2d6 fire<br/><b>Str </b>13, <b>Dex </b>14, <b>Con </b>13, <b>Int </b>10, <b>Wis </b>11, <b>Cha </b>10"
                        }
                    ],
                    "html": "LE dragon (fire)"
                }
            ],
            "html": "<b>Source</b><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"http://paizo.com/products/btpy8odu?Pathfinder-Roleplaying-Game-Bestiary-3\" target=\"_blank\"><i>Bestiary 3 pg. 102</i></a><br/><i>This serpentine dragon has skin the color of deep volcanic rock, enormous claws, and jagged, stonelike horns and scales.</i><br/><br/>Although chromatic and metallic dragons are the most widely known, other categories of true dragon exist. Presented here are the five imperial dragons, regal guardians of ancient lands and servants of cosmic balance."
        }
